			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-509431">
				April 25, 2017 at 15:01					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>Worldcon 75 Helsinki is working on arranging for an package of finalists. This is dependent upon the individual rights-holders being willing to provide such works, and they are not required to do so. When Worldcon 75 has a package available, they will make an announcement, and we will also post an announcement here on the Hugo Awards web site.</p>
<p>(Arranging such packages is done by each individual Worldcon committee, not by the Hugo Awards web site. Worldcons are not required to attempt to create such packages. They are provides solely through the goodwill of the individual rights holders. It is unlikely that such a package would ever be made as a paid package, due to the large number of rights-holders involved in such a package.)</p>
</div>

