				<div class="comment-body"><p>Madelyn:</p>
<p>The Hugo Award was first presented at the 1953 World Science Fiction Convention. The &#8220;how&#8221; is that the committee of the 1953 Worldcon decided to present awards. Although initially considered as a one-time event, in 1955 they were established as an annual award presented by the members of the World Science Fiction Society (i.e. the members of Worldcon). See the <a href="../../about/index.html">Introduction to the Hugo Award</a> page for more information.</p>
<p>Kevin Standlee</p>
</div>

