				<div class="comment-body"><p>Kevin:</p>
<p>I&#8217;m sorry, but for some reason your question went into our spam trap and we didn&#8217;t see it until now.</p>
<p>The question you raise is a difficult one. The rules for Best Graphic Story, as with most other &#8220;story&#8221; categories, assume that there are defined stories with a beginning and and end. Therefore, a serialized graphic story (which is what a comic/webcomic is) has to have a point where the creator says &#8220;end of story&#8221; (not &#8220;end of comic,&#8221; but &#8220;place where this story ends&#8221;). The Best Graphic Story category is not a &#8220;Best Webcomic&#8221; or &#8220;Best Comic Book Series&#8221; category, but instead is intended to honor a specific story with a beginning and an end.</p>
</div>

